Clearing fronts from memory
---------------------------
Here is a neat way to clear any fonts from memory that
are not being used. It's a procedure that tries to reserve
a huge amount of memory, and creates an "out of
memory" report. This forces the Amiga to perform a
"garbage collection" which gets rid of your unwanted
fonts automatically.


Procedure WIPE_FONTS
  On Error Goto SKIP
  Erase 15 : Reserve As Work 15,10000000
  SKIP: Resume SKIP2
  SKIP2:
End Proc


