Using the semi-colon causes your data to be printed
immediately after the previous value, but a comma
moves the cursor to the next "Tab" position on the
screen. A tab is an automatic marker that sets up a
location for printing, and is often used to lay out columns
of figures, or to make indentations in text. The use of the
